# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type(s):
#   feat:      Nouvelle fonctionnalité (MINOR bump)
#   fix:       Correction de bug (PATCH bump)
#   perf:      Amélioration performance (PATCH bump)
#   docs:      Documentation (NO release)
#   style:     Formatage (NO release)
#   refactor:  Refactoring (NO release)
#   test:      Tests (NO release)
#   build:     Build system (NO release)
#   ci:        CI/CD (NO release)
#   chore:     Maintenance (NO release)
#   revert:    Revert (PATCH bump)
#
# Scope: components of your code affected
#   Examples: auth, chat, tasks, notifications, dashboard, db, api
#
# Subject:
#   - Use lowercase
#   - No period at the end
#   - Imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# Body:
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Can be multiple paragraphs
#
# Footer:
#   - BREAKING CHANGE: description
#   - Closes #123, #456
#   - Refs #789
#
# Examples:
#   feat(auth): add OAuth Google provider
#   fix(chat): resolve message ordering issue
#   perf(queries): optimize user lookup with indexes
#   feat(api)!: migrate REST API to GraphQL
#
#   BREAKING CHANGE: All REST endpoints removed
